<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-31T22:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-31T22:40:00-05:00" n="279" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1124.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-31T23:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1914, 11 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Lower House of Congress filibustering against passage of legislation
                            attempt to control apportionment of representation in electoral college,
                            no election being possible until such apportionment. The filibustering
                            is intended to prevent election before April 30th. Parties opposed to
                            Government proposing to claim office of President vacant after 30th,
                            however. Government reports serious fighting begun at La Vega and
                            Santiago.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>